27
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:45,530
Hey, Mr. Phatsa!

28
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:46,410
Mr. Nakhun?

29
00:01:46,539 --> 00:01:47,850
I heard

30
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:51,000
the eldest son of the Devathitirat family

31
00:01:51,020 --> 00:01:52,860
bit an Omega on the neck.

32
00:01:53,690 --> 00:01:55,289
There's nothing

33
00:01:55,470 --> 00:01:56,600
between us anymore.

34
00:01:57,570 --> 00:01:59,570
Take off your shirt and give it to me.

35
00:02:19,410 --> 00:02:21,410
What were you doing in the restroom?

36
00:02:21,810 --> 00:02:23,470
I was just using the restroom.

37
00:02:29,910 --> 00:02:31,770
Then why did you call my name?

38
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:37,040
I didn't.

39
00:02:38,110 --> 00:02:39,440
You must have misheard.

40
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:42,950
You clearly said "Phatsa."

41
00:03:00,470 --> 00:03:00,970
I...

42
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,470
I said "Pasta."

43
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:09,600
I was going to have Sila deliver pasta.

44
00:03:11,170 --> 00:03:11,970
Really?

45
00:03:24,170 --> 00:03:25,440
Do you want to hold me?

46
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:31,570
You're the one who wouldn't let me.

47
00:03:32,970 --> 00:03:33,829
Then what if...

48
00:03:38,410 --> 00:03:39,630
I let you?

49
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:43,370
Phatsa, I'll always respect you.

50
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:47,110
As long as you don't give me permission,

51
00:03:48,410 --> 00:03:50,240
I have no right to touch you.

52
00:04:17,209 --> 00:04:20,250
So you don't want to hold me?

53
00:04:34,610 --> 00:04:35,700
Phatsa, don't mess

54
00:04:35,730 --> 00:04:36,810
with my feelings.

55
00:04:38,870 --> 00:04:40,130
Because if you say yes,

56
00:04:43,470 --> 00:04:44,800
I'll take it seriously.

57
00:05:11,570 --> 00:05:13,040
Don't do this, Phatsa.

58
00:05:19,270 --> 00:05:21,670
You have no idea
how hard it is to resist you.

59
00:05:49,610 --> 00:05:50,540
But I...

60
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,510
want you to hold me.

61
00:06:02,310 --> 00:06:03,110
Phatsa.

62
00:06:04,910 --> 00:06:06,310
Are you in Heat right now?

63
00:06:11,470 --> 00:06:12,640
I don't know.

64
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:18,530
I don't know what's wrong with me.

65
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:31,550
I'm burning up.

66
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,210
Calm down, Phatsa.

67
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,240
This is insane.

68
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:32,400
I was the one
who wouldn't let you touch me,

69
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,900
but now I'm the one making the first move.

70
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:45,409
I have feelings for you.

71
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:49,270
It's different from the first time.

72
00:08:01,810 --> 00:08:03,140
Are you sure about this?

73
00:08:39,929 --> 00:08:41,590
I won't take advantage of you.

74
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:49,070
Phatsa.

75
00:13:03,910 --> 00:13:04,890
Are you awake?

76
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:15,240
Don't be shy.

77
00:13:18,370 --> 00:13:19,670
This is a normal instinctive reaction

78
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:21,330
between an Alpha and an Omega.

79
00:13:25,710 --> 00:13:27,510
You and I are soulmates.

80
00:13:29,970 --> 00:13:31,170
That's why our reaction is much stronger

81
00:13:31,170 --> 00:13:33,370
than that of regular Alphas and Omegas.

82
00:13:40,810 --> 00:13:42,370
We're soulmates?

83
00:13:43,670 --> 00:13:45,370
It's also called Fated Mate.

84
00:13:46,470 --> 00:13:47,730
It's incredibly rare.

85
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:54,210
There's an incredibly
strong attraction between us.

86
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:57,630
That's why I lost control
and bit your neck that day.

87
00:14:00,270 --> 00:14:01,530
But I'm glad it was you.

88
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,040
Why?

89
00:14:15,570 --> 00:14:17,010
Am I your type?

90
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:21,130
I don't really have a type.

91
00:14:33,470 --> 00:14:34,810
What about your exes?

92
00:14:36,510 --> 00:14:37,640
What were they like?

93
00:14:38,770 --> 00:14:40,170
I've never dated anyone.

94
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:47,170
You're telling me
you've never dated anyone?

95
00:14:52,310 --> 00:14:53,740
You're so handsome,

96
00:14:55,310 --> 00:14:56,910
and your family is so rich...

97
00:15:00,370 --> 00:15:01,970
Are you frigid or something?

98
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:06,770
I'm not frigid.

99
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,100
You know that better than anyone.

100
00:15:16,370 --> 00:15:20,610
Whenever I wanted sex,

101
00:15:26,510 --> 00:15:28,970
Sila would have people
sent to my hotel room.

102
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:50,040
Was one not enough for you?

103
00:16:19,910 --> 00:16:21,010
Hey.

104
00:16:24,970 --> 00:16:26,970
You really don't have to come see me.

105
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:31,040
I really don't care about
what happened that day anymore.

106
00:16:32,910 --> 00:16:37,610
Just don't come see me again from now on.

107
00:16:39,180 --> 00:16:39,980
No.

108
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:44,610
I want to see you.

109
00:16:50,970 --> 00:16:54,230
Can you please not be mad at me
about what happened that day?

110
00:16:58,310 --> 00:16:59,970
I only did it to make you stop.

111
00:17:01,810 --> 00:17:04,369
Maybe I was too stupid to do that.

112
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,839
It seems I went against your wishes too.

113
00:17:11,970 --> 00:17:13,700
It never should have happened.

114
00:17:16,170 --> 00:17:17,170
Anyway,

115
00:17:19,869 --> 00:17:20,710
I'm sorry.

116
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,900
Didn't I already tell you?

117
00:17:28,610 --> 00:17:30,270
I don't care about it anymore.

118
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:34,840
But there's something
I have to tell you today.

119
00:17:35,210 --> 00:17:36,210
What is it?

120
00:17:38,510 --> 00:17:39,610
I want to court you.

121
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:46,210
Are you crazy?

122
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:49,640
I'm not. I just want to court you.

123
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:54,660
Why do you want to court a Beta like me?

124
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:58,270
You're a True Alpha.

125
00:17:59,470 --> 00:18:03,810
I think you should be with an Omega,

126
00:18:05,910 --> 00:18:07,310
not a Beta like me.

127
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:10,240
What's wrong with Betas?

128
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:12,790
Alpha, Omega, or Beta—

129
00:18:12,820 --> 00:18:14,880
we're all human in the end, aren't we?

130
00:18:17,470 --> 00:18:19,450
I've never understood

131
00:18:20,150 --> 00:18:22,350
why you insist on living by those rules.

132
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:23,780
Because you're from

133
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:25,370
the Devathitirat family.

134
00:18:27,210 --> 00:18:28,320
In the end,

135
00:18:28,340 --> 00:18:31,450
your family will still
make you marry an Omega,

136
00:18:34,270 --> 00:18:36,470
just like every generation before you.

137
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:38,840
You even know about my family?

138
00:18:46,110 --> 00:18:47,380
Hmm...

139
00:18:49,210 --> 00:18:51,730
You look refreshed.

140
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:56,040
Alright, go back to work now.

141
00:18:58,170 --> 00:19:00,340
Uh, don't rush me yet.

142
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:01,920
I start taking customers

143
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:03,450
before the café even opens.

144
00:19:04,510 --> 00:19:06,770
Then where are these customers of yours?

145
00:19:07,570 --> 00:19:09,500
Isn't this my customer right here?

146
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:14,810
I missed you so much!

147
00:19:17,410 --> 00:19:18,670
Is this your son?

148
00:19:21,420 --> 00:19:23,940
No, this is my cousin.

149
00:19:23,970 --> 00:19:26,030
Come on, introduce yourself, Japan.

150
00:19:26,370 --> 00:19:27,910
Hello, my name is Japan.

151
00:19:29,410 --> 00:19:31,320
He's my uncle's son.

152
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:33,610
We're really close, aren't we?

153
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:37,800
Yes, but you haven't
come to see me lately.

154
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,850
I was planning to see you.

155
00:19:39,870 --> 00:19:41,310
How about this Saturday?

156
00:19:41,670 --> 00:19:43,160
Nakhun and I

157
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:44,510
will take you golfing.

158
00:19:45,010 --> 00:19:46,280
No need.

159
00:19:46,770 --> 00:19:47,840
It'll be scorching.

160
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:49,840
Then we'll go to the shooting range.

161
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:50,640
Well...

162
00:19:51,210 --> 00:19:52,210
it's a deal, then.

163
00:19:54,210 --> 00:19:55,010
Deal.

164
00:19:55,410 --> 00:19:56,810
Order whatever you want.

165
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:58,570
But there's one condition.

166
00:20:00,210 --> 00:20:02,410
You have to treat me, because I'm broke.

167
00:20:02,670 --> 00:20:03,810
I'm broke too.

168
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:06,730
I'm joking. Go wait over there first.

169
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:22,010
Well, thank you in advance.

170
00:20:35,770 --> 00:20:38,300
He'll definitely like
the flowers I gave him.

171
00:20:44,670 --> 00:20:45,840
How's this?

172
00:20:57,670 --> 00:20:59,470
Help me look over these numbers.

173
00:21:00,270 --> 00:21:01,470
Something seems off.

174
00:21:08,070 --> 00:21:09,670
Have Sila do it for you.

175
00:21:19,510 --> 00:21:21,640
Didn't you say you'd help me with work?

176
00:21:23,470 --> 00:21:24,930
I don't feel like it today.

177
00:21:26,210 --> 00:21:27,740
Why are you always sulking?

178
00:21:29,670 --> 00:21:30,710
I'm not sulking.

179
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:32,440
Sila.

180
00:21:34,070 --> 00:21:35,310
What do you think?

181
00:21:38,910 --> 00:21:40,400
I'm not working today.

182
00:21:40,670 --> 00:21:42,950
Then, why not help Madam cook?

183
00:21:43,670 --> 00:21:44,730
Today's my day off.

184
00:21:45,010 --> 00:21:46,020
Normally, Madam Kampirada

185
00:21:46,020 --> 00:21:48,070
cooks for Mr. Nakhun herself.

186
00:21:49,070 --> 00:21:50,910
Then let's help Mom cook.

187
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:52,510
This way, please.

188
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:12,910
The potatoes are really nice today.

189
00:22:13,970 --> 00:22:15,160
Oh, right here.

190
00:22:15,470 --> 00:22:16,670
This way, Mr. Phatsa.

191
00:22:18,970 --> 00:22:20,050
Well...

192
00:22:20,110 --> 00:22:21,370
do we still need anything, Jim?

193
00:22:21,370 --> 00:22:22,500
No, I don't think so.

194
00:22:22,510 --> 00:22:23,310
Hmm.

195
00:22:23,570 --> 00:22:24,270
Everything's ready.

196
00:22:24,270 --> 00:22:25,670
Mom, what are you making?

197
00:22:27,110 --> 00:22:29,970
I'm making beef massaman curry.

198
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:32,540
It's one of Nakhun's favorite dishes.

199
00:22:32,770 --> 00:22:33,570
So...

200
00:22:33,770 --> 00:22:35,500
Phatsa, can you help me make it?

201
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:41,810
Sure, but Mom, I've never cooked before.

202
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:45,040
That's okay. It's easy. I will teach you.

203
00:22:47,470 --> 00:22:53,040
Mom, does massaman curry use cashews?

204
00:22:53,410 --> 00:22:55,620
Normally we'd use peanuts,

205
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:57,410
but Nakhun doesn't eat peanuts.

206
00:22:57,410 --> 00:23:00,210
So I use cashews instead.

207
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:01,970
Such a picky eater.

208
00:23:02,610 --> 00:23:03,580
What did you say?

209
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:06,570
Nothing, Mom. Let me help you.

210
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:12,250
All right. Help me chop the potatoes then.

211
00:23:13,370 --> 00:23:14,040
This one?

212
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:16,070
Yes, cut it like this.

213
00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:20,150
Like this, right?

214
00:23:25,570 --> 00:23:26,430
Ah!

215
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:35,940
Are you okay?

216
00:23:37,570 --> 00:23:38,670
First-aid kit!

217
00:23:38,740 --> 00:23:40,770
It's here. Open it, hurry!

218
00:23:40,770 --> 00:23:42,370
Open it quickly.

219
00:23:42,370 --> 00:23:43,040
Don't grab it.

220
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:44,010
Open it, now!

221
00:23:44,140 --> 00:23:45,270
-Let me see.
-What?

222
00:23:45,270 --> 00:23:46,270
Do we need saline?

223
00:23:47,370 --> 00:23:49,060
And then? What do we do next?

224
00:23:50,770 --> 00:23:51,270
Cotton.

225
00:23:51,270 --> 00:23:53,010
Cotton? Isn't this it?

226
00:23:53,210 --> 00:23:54,170
Let me do it.

227
00:23:55,770 --> 00:23:58,110
Nakhun, I'm so sorry.

228
00:23:58,130 --> 00:23:59,400
He wanted to help me make

229
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,510
your favorite beef massaman curry

230
00:24:01,610 --> 00:24:03,940
so that he can
cook it for you in the future.

231
00:24:04,370 --> 00:24:05,770
Who wants to cook for him?

232
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,570
Let those women
at his hotel room cook for him.

233
00:24:15,810 --> 00:24:16,930
Don't be mad at me.

234
00:24:17,510 --> 00:24:19,010
That was a long time ago.

235
00:24:20,010 --> 00:24:20,810
And now,

236
00:24:22,170 --> 00:24:24,830
I don't feel that way
about anyone else anymore.

237
00:24:26,710 --> 00:24:28,770
I only have feelings for you, Phatsa.

238
00:24:34,670 --> 00:24:35,660
Oh, come on.

239
00:24:39,310 --> 00:24:42,350
Ouch! Mom.

240
00:24:42,510 --> 00:24:43,280
What is it?

241
00:24:43,670 --> 00:24:44,840
Phatsa hit me.

242
00:24:44,870 --> 00:24:49,310
Good. You deserve it for being so naughty.

243
00:24:54,310 --> 00:24:55,630
Thank you.

244
00:24:59,510 --> 00:25:01,090
Let's eat.

245
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:07,760
Naphitch, Mom's talking to you.

246
00:25:07,780 --> 00:25:09,240
Why aren't you answering?

247
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:12,840
I'm not hungry yet.

248
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:18,070
You're getting more and more out of line.

249
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:21,320
That's enough, both of you.

250
00:25:35,470 --> 00:25:36,570
Mr. Naphitch,

251
00:25:37,310 --> 00:25:41,070
I think you should be more polite.

252
00:25:41,710 --> 00:25:44,710
When an elder speaks to you
or asks you to do something,

253
00:25:45,410 --> 00:25:46,390
you should respond.

254
00:25:46,390 --> 00:25:49,390
That's the basic courtesy
of a well-mannered person.

255
00:25:49,870 --> 00:25:52,040
Don't ignore your elders like that.

256
00:25:57,240 --> 00:26:00,110
You should calm down as well.

257
00:26:00,130 --> 00:26:03,970
Constantly scolding him
won't make things better.

258
00:26:04,740 --> 00:26:05,640
It will only

259
00:26:06,210 --> 00:26:07,870
make him more rebellious.

260
00:26:08,130 --> 00:26:09,460
Who do you think you are?

261
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,640
What gives you the right to lecture me?

262
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:13,380
You're just an Omega,

263
00:26:13,510 --> 00:26:15,440
living under someone else's roof.

264
00:26:16,170 --> 00:26:18,170
And you dare meddle in our business?

265
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,870
I'll tell Dad right now

266
00:26:20,170 --> 00:26:22,370
and have him throw you out of this house!

267
00:26:30,010 --> 00:26:31,210
Go ahead and try.

268
00:26:31,510 --> 00:26:33,370
I can leave here anytime.

269
00:26:34,470 --> 00:26:37,890
I have somewhere to go,
and I can support myself.

270
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:39,840
Unlike someone else,

271
00:26:40,470 --> 00:26:42,120
who lives in this house

272
00:26:42,610 --> 00:26:45,040
but shows no respect for the family.

273
00:26:46,170 --> 00:26:47,770
I'm not being presumptuous.

274
00:26:49,010 --> 00:26:49,830
I'm only saying this

275
00:26:49,830 --> 00:26:52,170
because you're Nakhun's younger brother.

276
00:26:52,170 --> 00:26:53,390
That's why I reminded you, as someone

277
00:26:53,390 --> 00:26:55,270
who lives in this house too.

278
00:26:56,070 --> 00:26:57,320
If I didn't care,

279
00:26:58,020 --> 00:27:00,310
or if I thought we had nothing
to do with each other,

280
00:27:00,310 --> 00:27:03,470
I wouldn't even bother
saying a word to you!

281
00:27:16,870 --> 00:27:17,670
Let's eat.

282
00:27:34,540 --> 00:27:36,100
Mom, I'm sorry.

283
00:27:37,360 --> 00:27:38,160
It's okay.

284
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:41,700
Phatsa, you did very well.

285
00:27:49,210 --> 00:27:50,270
Let's eat.

286
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:58,210
Massaman curry.

287
00:27:58,670 --> 00:28:00,210
Mom said you like it.

288
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:06,120
Excuse me.

289
00:28:07,370 --> 00:28:11,110
Mr. Nakhun, there's an
urgent call from the company.

290
00:28:23,670 --> 00:28:27,370
Mom, I'll go deal with something first.

291
00:28:28,410 --> 00:28:31,510
You're not eating first?

292
00:28:33,070 --> 00:28:34,930
It's truly urgent at the company.

293
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:38,470
Phatsa, can you save some for me?

294
00:28:38,970 --> 00:28:40,300
I'll be back to eat soon.

295
00:28:40,870 --> 00:28:41,670
I promise.

296
00:28:52,270 --> 00:28:53,510
Don't make that face.

297
00:28:54,640 --> 00:28:56,300
I'll come back as soon as I can.

298
00:28:59,010 --> 00:29:00,370
Go ahead.

299
00:29:02,870 --> 00:29:04,130
Come home early, okay?

300
00:29:05,770 --> 00:29:06,770
I'll wait for you.

301
00:29:10,270 --> 00:29:10,810
Okay.

302
00:29:14,210 --> 00:29:15,270
I'm leaving now.

303
00:29:43,810 --> 00:29:45,470
Are you trying to pick a fight?

304
00:29:47,970 --> 00:29:49,070
Watch your tone.

305
00:29:50,510 --> 00:29:51,910
Or should I say

306
00:29:53,210 --> 00:29:54,370
what you just did

307
00:29:55,170 --> 00:29:57,870
is your idea of good manners?

308
00:30:01,420 --> 00:30:05,380
Looks like you were raised very well.

309
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:04,970
Not eating, are you?

310
00:31:05,430 --> 00:31:08,650
Fine. I'll feed it to the dogs.

311
00:31:22,910 --> 00:31:23,760
They said it was

312
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:25,320
someone from

313
00:31:25,350 --> 00:31:26,750
the Jirapapawong Group.

314
00:31:28,170 --> 00:31:29,440
Call Amintra over.

315
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:31,440
Yes, sir.

316
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:39,440
Who are you?
Why did you go to that warehouse?

317
00:31:40,310 --> 00:31:42,410
I don't know what you're talking about.

318
00:31:42,410 --> 00:31:44,210
Don't put on an act in front of me.

319
00:31:45,660 --> 00:31:46,860
I was just passing by.

320
00:31:48,070 --> 00:31:51,200
Just passing by?
You went all the way into the warehouse.

321
00:31:51,410 --> 00:31:53,810
What were you doing at Nakhun's warehouse?

322
00:31:54,170 --> 00:31:55,170
Not talking, huh?

323
00:31:57,340 --> 00:31:58,720
Hey, Miss Amintra.

324
00:32:01,910 --> 00:32:04,270
I'm fine. Go ahead then.

325
00:32:05,070 --> 00:32:06,710
Don't! Don't shoot!

326
00:32:06,710 --> 00:32:08,180
I'll talk, I'll talk!

327
00:32:08,470 --> 00:32:09,270
Talk!

328
00:32:10,210 --> 00:32:11,650
I went in...

329
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:13,210
because Kingyok told me to.

330
00:32:15,370 --> 00:32:16,310
Kingyok?

331
00:32:17,310 --> 00:32:20,520
Yes. She ordered me to.
I was just following orders.

332
00:32:21,410 --> 00:32:24,210
What did Kingyok ask you
to get from the warehouse?

333
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:25,720
I don't know.

334
00:32:26,510 --> 00:32:28,110
I was just following orders.

335
00:32:31,370 --> 00:32:33,230
No damage has been done this time,

336
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:34,900
so I won't call the police.

337
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:40,370
Go back and settle it with your people.

338
00:32:41,570 --> 00:32:42,970
I'll handle this myself.

339
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:18,150
Young master, please eat something.

340
00:33:21,410 --> 00:33:22,180
Sila!

341
00:33:27,170 --> 00:33:28,190
Young master.

342
00:33:30,820 --> 00:33:31,930
I'm fine.

343
00:33:34,610 --> 00:33:35,870
Are you okay?

344
00:33:40,370 --> 00:33:41,440
I'm fine now.

345
00:33:48,710 --> 00:33:49,950
The wound has been treated.

346
00:33:49,950 --> 00:33:52,890
Keep the wound dry
and watch for signs of infection.

347
00:33:53,670 --> 00:33:54,310
Thank you.

348
00:33:54,340 --> 00:33:54,870
Alright.

349
00:34:11,070 --> 00:34:14,040
I was ambushed on the way back
from the police station.

350
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:15,570
You don't need to come over.

351
00:34:15,710 --> 00:34:16,510
I'm fine.

352
00:34:16,770 --> 00:34:18,570
I called you to keep a lid on this.

353
00:34:19,170 --> 00:34:21,020
Don't let it get out of hand.

354
00:34:21,310 --> 00:34:23,770
Don't forget
to bring my medicine tomorrow.

355
00:34:24,409 --> 00:34:25,739
I'm going back to sleep.

356
00:34:26,310 --> 00:34:27,310
I'm done waiting.

357
00:34:37,639 --> 00:34:39,440
Why didn't you answer the phone?

358
00:34:54,750 --> 00:34:56,909
Phatsa, you should eat first.

359
00:34:56,940 --> 00:34:58,790
Nakhun will be back soon.

360
00:35:01,370 --> 00:35:07,570
Okay, Mom, but I want
to wait a little longer.

361
00:35:08,210 --> 00:35:11,640
Don't forget to eat. I'm leaving now.

362
00:36:13,010 --> 00:36:14,210
You're back, my dear.

363
00:36:15,710 --> 00:36:19,310
Why are you back so late?
You didn't answer your phone last night.

364
00:36:19,810 --> 00:36:20,610
I'm sorry.

365
00:36:21,970 --> 00:36:22,770
Because...

366
00:36:24,070 --> 00:36:25,110
there was an emergency

367
00:36:25,110 --> 00:36:27,040
at the Rangsit construction site,

368
00:36:27,270 --> 00:36:30,470
so I was dealing with it until late.

369
00:36:33,110 --> 00:36:35,510
I found a hotel nearby
and stayed there last night.

370
00:36:35,510 --> 00:36:37,970
I was too exhausted
to drive home last night.

371
00:36:39,040 --> 00:36:42,010
I thought you were in trouble.

372
00:36:42,010 --> 00:36:45,770
If you're staying at a hotel
instead of coming home,

373
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,490
just give me a heads-up.

374
00:36:49,370 --> 00:36:50,900
I'm going to my room to rest.

375
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:52,840
Go ahead.

376
00:37:56,460 --> 00:37:57,590
Where have you been?

377
00:37:59,810 --> 00:38:02,010
You weren't even going to tell me at all?

378
00:38:08,770 --> 00:38:10,230
I want to get some rest now.

379
00:38:26,210 --> 00:38:26,910
Why did you

380
00:38:26,940 --> 00:38:29,000
send someone to Nakhun's warehouse?

381
00:38:32,070 --> 00:38:32,770
I...

382
00:38:34,140 --> 00:38:35,410
I didn't.

383
00:38:36,610 --> 00:38:39,080
The police asked me to give a statement.

384
00:38:39,100 --> 00:38:42,250
Because the suspect gave them my name.

385
00:38:44,410 --> 00:38:45,410
I'm sorry!

386
00:38:46,310 --> 00:38:48,810
I didn't think
it would become this serious.

387
00:38:50,170 --> 00:38:51,830
I just didn't want you to lose.

388
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:54,970
I wanted you to win this bid.

389
00:38:55,110 --> 00:38:56,970
So that's how you chose to make it?

390
00:39:02,070 --> 00:39:05,100
What you did wasn't helping me at all.

391
00:39:07,370 --> 00:39:08,380
I just...

392
00:39:11,370 --> 00:39:12,630
wanted to protect you.

393
00:39:14,110 --> 00:39:15,770
I'm only an Omega.

394
00:39:16,410 --> 00:39:17,670
I know exactly who I am.

395
00:39:18,710 --> 00:39:20,510
Even though what I did was wrong,

396
00:39:21,240 --> 00:39:23,080
I only wanted you to win.

397
00:39:37,270 --> 00:39:39,840
I never wanted you to do this for me.

398
00:39:40,410 --> 00:39:41,530
And I would never think

399
00:39:41,530 --> 00:39:44,460
you are beneath anyone
just because you're an Omega.

400
00:39:44,970 --> 00:39:48,910
But what you did today made me realize

401
00:39:49,770 --> 00:39:51,770
that you don't believe in me either.

402
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:54,770
That's not true.

403
00:39:55,310 --> 00:39:56,370
I do believe in you.

404
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:58,920
I really do.

405
00:39:59,670 --> 00:40:02,100
If you believed I was capable enough,

406
00:40:02,470 --> 00:40:04,800
you wouldn't have used such a dirty trick.

407
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:06,240
I'm sorry.

408
00:40:07,810 --> 00:40:09,420
I'm truly sorry.

409
00:40:12,240 --> 00:40:14,140
I'm not afraid of losing.

410
00:40:14,170 --> 00:40:18,810
I'm just afraid
that you'll think I'm not good enough—

411
00:40:19,570 --> 00:40:21,120
not good enough that I have to

412
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:23,450
let someone else solve everything for me.

413
00:40:38,310 --> 00:40:39,610
Oh, Phatsa.

414
00:40:39,630 --> 00:40:41,560
Didn't Nakhun come with you today?

415
00:40:42,010 --> 00:40:43,470
Then who did you come with?

416
00:40:43,700 --> 00:40:44,820
Melda, Jenny, and I

417
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:45,910
came together.

418
00:40:45,940 --> 00:40:48,970
We agreed to eat at Ongsa's café.

419
00:40:49,870 --> 00:40:52,050
Phatsa is so handsome.

420
00:40:52,070 --> 00:40:53,950
Are you an Alpha?

421
00:40:55,010 --> 00:40:57,810
No, he's an Omega.

422
00:40:58,070 --> 00:40:58,830
Really?

423
00:40:58,850 --> 00:41:00,910
But he looks like an Alpha.

424
00:41:01,170 --> 00:41:01,970
Totally.

425
00:41:02,310 --> 00:41:04,510
He's just the most handsome Omega.

426
00:41:04,870 --> 00:41:06,320
I think so too.

427
00:41:06,350 --> 00:41:08,560
Whenever I'm with Phatsa,

428
00:41:08,590 --> 00:41:11,240
I feel especially safe.

429
00:41:12,010 --> 00:41:14,840
Really, you're incredibly handsome.

430
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:16,500
If Ongsa hadn't

431
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:18,060
told me you were an Omega,

432
00:41:18,090 --> 00:41:20,150
I would've thought you were an Alpha.

433
00:41:21,810 --> 00:41:23,270
At first, I thought so too.

434
00:41:23,910 --> 00:41:26,970
We should get going.
We have horseback riding lessons.

435
00:41:27,710 --> 00:41:32,310
Okay. See you. Take care.

436
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:39,410
How are you going to get there?

437
00:41:39,410 --> 00:41:40,870
By helicopter.

438
00:41:41,910 --> 00:41:42,770
He's so rich.

439
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:51,510
Is Nakhun with you?

440
00:41:51,770 --> 00:41:54,130
I've called him several times,
but he won't answer.

441
00:41:54,130 --> 00:41:57,660
I don't know. Maybe he's too tired.

442
00:41:58,210 --> 00:42:01,470
He didn't come home last night.
He said he stayed at a hotel.

443
00:42:01,710 --> 00:42:04,740
What hotel?
He was clearly at the hospital.

444
00:42:06,610 --> 00:42:08,910
The hospital? Why?

445
00:42:09,910 --> 00:42:10,820
Last night,

446
00:42:10,840 --> 00:42:12,330
on the way back from Rangsit,

447
00:42:12,330 --> 00:42:13,310
he got shot.

448
00:42:13,340 --> 00:42:14,370
Shot?

449
00:42:16,070 --> 00:42:18,810
Why didn't he tell me he'd been shot?

450
00:42:19,640 --> 00:42:21,010
How would I know?

451
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:25,020
By the way,
what medicine is he allergic to again?

452
00:42:25,410 --> 00:42:27,650
Never mind. I'll ask Mom.

453
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:29,810
You're at Ongsa's café now, right?

454
00:42:29,830 --> 00:42:31,490
I'll come find you right away.

455
00:42:40,270 --> 00:42:42,820
Take good care of yourself these days.

456
00:42:42,850 --> 00:42:45,050
Remember to take your medicine on time.

457
00:42:45,510 --> 00:42:47,570
Okay, Doctor. Thank you.

458
00:42:51,010 --> 00:42:53,930
[Pharmacy]

459
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:54,370
Oh, Mr. Saengnuea.

460
00:42:56,090 --> 00:43:00,360
[Pharmacy]

461
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:58,040
What are you doing here?

462
00:42:58,810 --> 00:43:00,010
Are you sick?

463
00:43:00,870 --> 00:43:03,840
No. I'm just here for a routine checkup.

464
00:43:03,940 --> 00:43:05,970
My heat is coming soon.

465
00:43:07,570 --> 00:43:09,670
But you don't look very well.

466
00:43:11,410 --> 00:43:12,920
That's common

467
00:43:12,950 --> 00:43:14,080
for an Omega like me.

468
00:43:14,170 --> 00:43:16,300
When my pheromones are out of balance,

469
00:43:16,610 --> 00:43:17,940
I get tired very easily.

470
00:43:19,010 --> 00:43:21,540
But you've got
your medicine already, right?

471
00:43:21,870 --> 00:43:23,440
Yes, I have.

472
00:43:23,440 --> 00:43:26,970
I was about to go home,
but I haven't been able to get a taxi yet.

473
00:43:27,470 --> 00:43:29,340
Then let me give you a ride.

474
00:43:30,140 --> 00:43:31,540
My car is parked outside.

475
00:43:31,810 --> 00:43:32,610
Really?

476
00:43:33,170 --> 00:43:34,970
But I need to go somewhere first.

477
00:43:35,970 --> 00:43:36,910
I'm meeting up with Phatsa

478
00:43:36,910 --> 00:43:38,310
at Ongsa's café.

479
00:43:38,970 --> 00:43:39,770
Sure.

480
00:43:41,040 --> 00:43:42,040
This way, please.

481
00:44:01,310 --> 00:44:02,640
What exactly happened?

482
00:44:04,370 --> 00:44:06,170
Nakhun was ambushed yesterday.

483
00:44:07,510 --> 00:44:08,440
What did you say?

484
00:44:08,670 --> 00:44:10,300
He was attacked again

485
00:44:10,330 --> 00:44:11,970
on his way home.

486
00:44:12,310 --> 00:44:13,870
To save Sila,

487
00:44:14,640 --> 00:44:15,670
he got shot.

488
00:44:16,020 --> 00:44:17,940
Huh? He was shot?

489
00:44:19,410 --> 00:44:20,740
But he's fine now.

490
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:23,930
A True Alpha is physically strong.

491
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:25,490
They don't die that easily.

492
00:44:27,670 --> 00:44:31,430
But Nakhun's so stubborn
that he refused to stay in the hospital.

493
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:33,790
That's why he only came home this morning.

494
00:44:34,770 --> 00:44:35,740
This morning,

495
00:44:37,070 --> 00:44:38,310
I didn't know that

496
00:44:39,980 --> 00:44:43,610
he was acting like that
because he was hurt. I thought...

497
00:44:46,410 --> 00:44:48,210
he was out last night because...

498
00:44:55,310 --> 00:44:56,110
Nakhun...

499
00:44:57,240 --> 00:44:58,240
I'm leaving now.

500
00:45:09,020 --> 00:45:13,230
Then... I'll go home by myself.

501
00:45:14,260 --> 00:45:16,540
No. You came with me.

502
00:45:17,790 --> 00:45:19,250
It's not very safe lately.

503
00:45:19,840 --> 00:45:23,010
But I don't want to trouble you.

504
00:45:23,570 --> 00:45:25,770
Don't mention it. I'm driving you home.

505
00:45:26,570 --> 00:45:29,010
Yes, just let Nakhin drive you home.

506
00:45:29,850 --> 00:45:31,090
Come with us, Ongsa.

507
00:45:31,470 --> 00:45:32,270
Huh?

508
00:45:33,430 --> 00:45:34,970
Let's take Saengnuea home together.

509
00:45:34,970 --> 00:45:36,570
I don't want to go home alone.

510
00:45:37,410 --> 00:45:39,180
It's just that the café...

511
00:45:39,210 --> 00:45:40,210
Just come with us.

512
00:45:42,240 --> 00:45:46,010
Sorry for causing
everyone so much trouble again.

513
00:45:46,870 --> 00:45:49,360
It's okay. Don't overthink it.

514
00:45:53,970 --> 00:45:55,520
Ongsa, come with us.

515
00:45:56,700 --> 00:45:59,030
Seeing Nakhin like this,

516
00:46:00,710 --> 00:46:01,410
I'm sure he'd want you

517
00:46:01,410 --> 00:46:03,140
to come home with us too, Ongsa.

518
00:46:06,270 --> 00:46:07,070
Hmm.

519
00:46:19,770 --> 00:46:20,570
Hey.

520
00:46:27,310 --> 00:46:28,110
Nakhun.

521
00:46:55,610 --> 00:46:56,640
It hurts again.

522
00:46:58,510 --> 00:47:00,370
The pain here just comes and goes,

523
00:47:02,110 --> 00:47:03,310
just like last night.

524
00:47:05,810 --> 00:47:06,610
And...

525
00:47:08,910 --> 00:47:10,910
why didn't you tell me you were shot?

526
00:47:11,910 --> 00:47:13,060
I'm fine now.

527
00:47:13,670 --> 00:47:15,040
How can you be fine?

528
00:47:15,840 --> 00:47:16,870
You were shot!

529
00:47:19,970 --> 00:47:20,770
And...

530
00:47:21,410 --> 00:47:22,940
you actually hid it from me!

531
00:47:23,840 --> 00:47:26,040
I only found out from Nakhin.

532
00:47:28,410 --> 00:47:30,040
The bullet just grazed me.

533
00:47:31,510 --> 00:47:33,210
It missed all my vital organs.

534
00:47:33,810 --> 00:47:35,270
The doctor said I was lucky

535
00:47:35,670 --> 00:47:37,470
that it only grazed my left side,

536
00:47:39,710 --> 00:47:41,510
and it was nowhere near my heart.

537
00:47:43,570 --> 00:47:46,940
It almost hit your heart!
How can you say it was nowhere near?

538
00:47:49,670 --> 00:47:51,740
It must hurt a lot.

539
00:47:52,650 --> 00:47:53,180
But...

540
00:47:55,540 --> 00:47:57,470
I kept hurting here last night too.

541
00:48:02,410 --> 00:48:03,210
Be careful.

542
00:48:07,510 --> 00:48:08,240
Does it hurt?

543
00:48:10,240 --> 00:48:11,180
Normally,

544
00:48:11,200 --> 00:48:14,670
an Alpha and Omega who have bonded

545
00:48:18,210 --> 00:48:20,010
don't share pain like this.

546
00:48:23,110 --> 00:48:25,170
Could it be because we're soulmates?

547
00:48:30,510 --> 00:48:31,770
Does it still hurt now?

548
00:48:35,490 --> 00:48:40,580
A little, but it's much better.

549
00:49:09,570 --> 00:49:14,410
I'll be more careful next time.

550
00:49:18,570 --> 00:49:20,970
Then you won't have to
suffer because of me.

551
00:49:25,710 --> 00:49:27,010
I'm sorry about this.

552
00:49:29,920 --> 00:49:31,720
I really had no choice back then.

553
00:49:33,240 --> 00:49:34,570
I had to save Sila.

554
00:49:38,670 --> 00:49:40,070
Hmm, it's okay.

555
00:49:42,540 --> 00:49:46,970
When I got hit by
that piece of wood at the warehouse,

556
00:49:50,040 --> 00:49:52,040
you must have felt the same pain too.

557
00:49:53,570 --> 00:49:55,230
I also should say sorry to you.

558
00:49:58,610 --> 00:50:02,410
How about this? From now on, both of us

559
00:50:02,440 --> 00:50:05,420
will take good care of ourselves.

560
00:50:08,810 --> 00:50:11,810
Then we won't have to
suffer like this together again.

561
00:50:18,810 --> 00:50:20,150
What am I supposed to do?

562
00:50:24,210 --> 00:50:25,770
I think you're really cute—

563
00:50:32,470 --> 00:50:33,640
cute enough to

564
00:50:36,170 --> 00:50:37,500
make me want to kiss you.

565
00:50:43,770 --> 00:50:46,510
Then what are you waiting for?

566
00:50:48,410 --> 00:50:50,270
Didn't you tell me not to kiss you?

567
00:51:01,110 --> 00:51:01,910
Silly.

568
00:51:33,610 --> 00:51:35,310
What a frustrating night. Don't you think?

569
00:51:34,090 --> 00:51:37,870
[In the next episode]

570
00:51:35,470 --> 00:51:38,210
Don't let these little things
ruin your mood.

571
00:51:38,370 --> 00:51:39,880
I heard a Pure Omega

572
00:51:39,910 --> 00:51:41,240
went to the hospital for a checkup.
Is that true?

573
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:43,290
But the patient's details
are confidential.

574
00:51:43,290 --> 00:51:44,870
They refuse to reveal
that person's identity.

575
00:51:44,870 --> 00:51:46,150
Go find out for me.

576
00:51:46,210 --> 00:51:47,810
I want to know who that kid is.

577
00:51:47,910 --> 00:51:49,110
What if I were a Beta?

578
00:51:49,410 --> 00:51:50,840
Would you still like me?

579
00:51:51,070 --> 00:51:53,270
Then we probably wouldn't be soulmates.

580
00:51:53,270 --> 00:51:54,440
Where's your friend?

581
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:55,610
Phatsa isn't here.

582
00:51:55,710 --> 00:51:56,630
He's right here.

583
00:51:56,630 --> 00:51:58,210
Nakhun's got the nose of a dog!

584
00:51:58,210 --> 00:52:01,470
He can tell exactly
where you're hiding just by your scent.

585
00:52:14,390 --> 00:52:18,330
♪ I linger in those beautiful memories ♪

586
00:52:18,350 --> 00:52:21,970
♪ I used to think we were meant to be ♪

587
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:23,620
♪ But I also know ♪

588
00:52:23,710 --> 00:52:27,600
♪ that reality isn't like that ♪

589
00:52:27,630 --> 00:52:31,930
♪ I tried so hard to keep you
from leaving ♪

590
00:52:32,040 --> 00:52:35,450
♪ But this broken love
is already shattered ♪

591
00:52:35,470 --> 00:52:41,930
♪ Because I always believed you would stay,
I'm willing to give up everything for you ♪

592
00:52:42,110 --> 00:52:47,610
♪ Had the best days ahead of us.
Turns out there are no more days ♪

593
00:52:47,690 --> 00:52:50,850
♪ left for us ♪

594
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:53,870
♪ Only memories remain ♪

595
00:52:53,890 --> 00:52:58,800
♪ How many more times do I have to hurt
to understand ♪

596
00:52:59,060 --> 00:53:02,040
♪ How much longer do I have to cry ♪

597
00:53:02,070 --> 00:53:06,780
♪ Before my heart tells me
it's time to let go ♪

598
00:53:06,800 --> 00:53:12,370
♪ If one day I leave ♪

599
00:53:12,520 --> 00:53:17,270
♪ You probably wouldn't feel a thing ♪

600
00:53:17,640 --> 00:53:22,390
♪ Like I never existed ♪

601
00:53:24,650 --> 00:53:28,010
♪ Not gonna lie, it hurt so much ♪

602
00:53:28,030 --> 00:53:31,340
♪ Not gonna lie, miss you so much ♪

603
00:53:31,490 --> 00:53:34,710
♪ If there was a little love left,
you wouldn't choose to leave ♪

604
00:53:34,980 --> 00:53:37,960
♪ But I don't know what's the point
of holding on ♪

605
00:53:37,980 --> 00:53:41,280
♪ My words and heart are always at odds ♪

606
00:53:41,300 --> 00:53:46,470
♪ No matter how much it hurts,
my heart won't listen. Not gonna lie ♪

607
